        "question": "What platforms support the sd CLI tool?",
        "answer": "sd works on macOS, Linux, and Windows via WSL. Install with 'brew install sd' on macOS or 'cargo install sd' cross-platform."
      },
      {
        "question": "How is sd different from sed?",
        "answer": "sd is global by default, uses simpler syntax without delimiters, and has better regex support without escaping slashes."
      },
      {
        "question": "Does this skill execute commands?",
        "answer": "No. This skill provides documentation and patterns. Users must have sd installed and execute commands through their terminal."
